OL,6,FTaylor Bradford was labelled "the
OL,7,Fgrand dame of blockbusters". Her books
OL,8,Fhave sold more than 91 million copies
OL,9,Fto date, and having been published in
OL,10,Fmore than 40 languages and in 90
OL,11,Fcountries.
OL,13,FBorn in Leeds in May 1933, she was the
OL,14,Fonly child of Winston and Freda Taylor.
OL,16,FShe began work as a typist for the
OL,17,FYorkshire Evening Post before she was
OL,18,Fpromoted to reporter and then went on
OL,19,Fto become the paper's first women's
OL,20,Feditor.
